# Make the body-slide "Київ, 2026" chrome badge background transparent

## Context

The screenshot the user attached shows a body slide where the top-left `Київ, 2026` badge rendered by `SlideChrome` sits inside a solid near-black rectangle on top of the deep-purple sonar stage. It reads as a dark box rather than a label integrated into the slide chrome. The user wants the badge's background to be transparent so the white text sits directly on the stage backdrop, matching the visual weight of the DOU logo on the right (which has no background fill).

Scope is intentionally limited to the chrome badge rendered by `SlideChrome` on every body slide. The title slide uses its own calibrated `.title-hero__tag` at stage (368, 390), which is pixel-matched to the DOU template and is out of scope for this change.

## Change

Single CSS property edit in `src/styles/slides.css` inside the `.slide-chrome__city-badge` rule (lines 857–873):

```diff
 .slide-chrome__city-badge {
   position: absolute;
   top: 27px;
   left: 55px;
   height: 84px;
   display: inline-flex;
   align-items: center;
   padding: 0 28px;
-  background: var(--dou-near-black);
+  background: transparent;
   color: var(--dou-white);
   ...
 }
```

No JSX, token, or component changes. `SlideChrome.tsx` is untouched. The title slide's `.title-hero__tag` (slides.css:906) keeps its `--dou-near-black` fill because it is calibrated to the DOU template and is not what the user flagged.

## Critical files

- `src/styles/slides.css` line 865 — the one-line CSS edit

## Verification

1. `bun run dev` (if not already running) — serve at http://localhost:5173/dou-days-2026/
2. Use the Chrome extension to open a body slide (e.g., the one in the screenshot — type `takeaways` or navigate to the appropriate slide number). Screenshot and confirm:
   - `Київ, 2026` text remains white, legible on the deep-purple + sonar backdrop
   - No visible rectangle around the text
   - Text position (top-left, 27px / 55px stage coords) is unchanged
3. Navigate to the title slide (slide 1) and confirm the hero-block `Київ, 2026` tag is still rendered with its dark fill (it should, since it is a different CSS rule).
4. Spot-check two other body slides with different sonar backdrops to confirm readability in each variant.

